filldraw(circle((0,0),7), lightgray, black+linewidth(1));
filldraw(circle((0,0),6), gray, black+linewidth(1));
filldraw(circle((0,0),4), white, black+linewidth(1));
dot((0,0));
label("$X$",(2,0));
label("$Y$",(5,0));
label("$Z$",(6.5,0));
[/asy]

Solution:
Step 1: Compute areas of the three regions.
- Inner disk (radius 4): A1 = π(4^2) = 16π.
- Middle annulus (radii 4 to 6): A2 = π(6^2 − 4^2) = π(36 − 16) = 20π.
- Outer annulus (radii 6 to 7): A3 = π(7^2 − 6^2) = π(49 − 36) = 13π.

Step 2: Identify greatest and smallest areas.
- Greatest: 20π (middle annulus)
- Smallest: 13π (outer annulus)

Step 3: Difference.
20π − 13π = 7π

\boxed{7\pi}

